cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel algorithm based on Spectral Residual (SR) and Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for time-series anomaly detection. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed algorithm is a form of AI for detecting anomalies in time-series data. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper borrows the SR model from visual saliency detection domain and applies it to time-series anomaly detection. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the pipeline and algorithm for data ingestion, experimentation platform, and online compute, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper describes the development of a time-series anomaly detection service at Microsoft, which involves software engineering principles and practices.
